\f0\fs32\b FWDE - Floating Windows Dynamic Equilibrium\b0\fs22\par
\par
Physics-based window management for Windows using AutoHotkey v2.\par
\par

\fs28\b What is FWDE? ("Fweddie")\b0\fs22\par
\par
FWDE automatically arranges floating windows using physics simulation. Windows repel each other to avoid overlap while staying within monitor bounds. Designed for workflows with multiple floating windows (DAW plugins, browser tabs, editor windows, terminals).\par
\par

\fs24\b DOWNLOAD FWDE.exe:\b0  \cf1\ul https://github.com/Flalaski/FWDE/releases\cf0\ulnone\par
\par

\fs28\b Features\b0\fs22\par
\par

\fs24\b Physics Engine\b0\par
\bullet  Attraction, repulsion, and damping forces\par
\bullet  Collision avoidance between windows\par
\bullet  Edge repulsion to fill screen space\par
\bullet  Configurable update rates and force parameters\par
\par

\fs24\b Multi-Monitor Support\b0\par
\bullet  Per-monitor physics calculations\par
\bullet  Optional cross-monitor mode (multimonitor expanse)\par
\bullet  Fullscreen detection to exclude games and media players\par
\bullet  Virtual desktop bounds for unified workspace\par
\par

\fs24\b Window Detection\b0\par
\bullet  Automatic detection by process name, window class, or title patterns\par
\bullet  Excludes system windows, taskbars, and fullscreen apps\par
\bullet  Manual force-add for any window\par
\bullet  Configurable inclusion patterns\par
\par

\fs24\b Manual Controls\b0\par
\bullet  Lock individual windows in position\par
\bullet  Optimize layout on demand\par
\bullet  Toggle physics and arrangement independently\par
\bullet  Pause lock during window drag, resume on release\par
\par

\fs24\b Debug Tools\b0\par
\bullet  Window analysis showing why windows are/aren't managed\par
\bullet  Pattern matching display\par
\bullet  Real-time tracking of managed windows\par
\bullet  Force-add capability for stubborn windows\par
\par

\fs28\b Installation\b0\fs22\par
\par

\fs24\b Requirements\b0\par
\bullet  Windows 7/8.1/10/11\par
\bullet  AutoHotkey v2 (only for building script manually, FWDE.exe in Releases is the app on its own)\par
\par

\fs24\b Setup\b0\par
1. Download \f1 FWDE.ahk\f0\par
2. Run directly with AutoHotkey v2, or compile to \f1 .exe\f0\par
3. Modify \f1 Config\f0  map at top of file (optional)\par
\par

\fs24\b Compilation\b0\par
\f1 autohotkey.exe /in FWDE.ahk\f0\par
\par

\fs28\b Usage\b0\fs22\par
\par
The system starts automatically when launched. Windows matching detection patterns are managed automatically. Use hotkeys for manual control.\par
\par
\bullet  \b Automatic\b0 : Eligible windows are detected and managed\par
\bullet  \b Lock window\b0 : \f1 Ctrl+Alt+L\f0  locks active window in place (33 second duration, auto-extends during drag)\par
\bullet  \b Force add\b0 : \f1 Ctrl+Alt+A\f0  manually adds active window to physics\par
\bullet  \b Optimize\b0 : \f1 Ctrl+Alt+O\f0  instantly rearranges all windows\par
\par

